# A wholly-constant expr value on a navigational URL sink that urlSanitize
# always blocks is knowable at generate time: warn (the render still fails
# closed to about:invalid#gsx — the warning converts the silent runtime
# failure into an actionable message, issue #154).
-- input.gsx --
package p

component Bad() {
	<a href={"javascript:alert(1)"}>x</a>
}
-- invoke --
Bad()
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:5: warning: constant href value "javascript:alert(1)" on <a> always sanitizes to about:invalid#gsx at render time; allowed schemes here are http/https/mailto/tel; vouch with gsx.RawURL if this value is intentional
-- render.golden --
<a href="about:invalid#gsx">x</a>
